member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.WebMedia.Protocols.FlexChatProtocol
member.summary: Channel opening can be performed in two ways depending on which channel parameters are set: 1) If UserId parameter is set, it means that user is already logged in. So channel will not send RequestLogin message to server during opening. SecureKey parameter should also be set in this case, otherwise server may not respond. 2) If UserId is not set, it means that user is not logged in, so server should send RequestLogin message during channel opening. UserNickName parameter is desirable to be set in this case. During channel opening after sending RequestLogin channel will wait for server response. If all is ok channel will fill UserId and SecureKey properties automatically. These UserId and SecureKey properties will be set in each user request (if they are not set manually) by channel automatically.

member.summary: Send the specified request to the server. To receive a response from the server, you must use the Genesyslab.Platform.Commons.Protocols.DuplexChannel.Receive() method. This response will be asynchronous. You can also use the Genesyslab.Platform.Commons.Protocols.ClientChannel.Request(Genesyslab.Platform.Commons.Protocols.IMessage) method instead of Send and Receive.
member.remarks: Current UserId, and SecureKey (if set) will be automatically added to any message, except RequestLogin message.
